> > Does Linux have support for > 8G.
> 
> Yes.
> 
> > will fdisk in Linux partition disks > 8G.
> 
> Yes.
> 
> >  if this is the appropriate mailing list,
> 
> No.
> 
> > pointer
> 
> For details, try reading the Large disk HOWTO.
> (Or just don't worry - all is fine by default.)
The Large Disk HOWTO doesn't cover disks over 8.4Gb (at least not last time I 
checked) - please see the following reference for complete info on getting 
past the 8.4Gb limit on kernels prior to 2.0.37pre4 and 2.2.1 (I think...):
http://www-oss.fnal.gov/fss/documentation/linux/linux-faq/
See both the entries on "how to format disks > 8.4gb" and "Large Disk Drives (>
8.4Gb)"
Cheers,
Dan
